@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Home Page";
}

<div class="text-center">
    <h1 class="display-4">Task Manager Application</h1>
    <p class="lead">A project developed as a demonstration of ASP.NET Core MVC capabilities.</p>
    
    <h3>Overview</h3>
    <p>
        This web application is a task management system that allows users to perform basic CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) operations
        on a list of tasks. Each task consists of a title and description stored in a PostgreSQL database. 
    </p>

    <h3>Key Features</h3>
    <ul class="text-start">
        <li><strong>View All Tasks:</strong> Users can see all tasks in a structured table format.</li>
        <li><strong>Create Task:</strong> Add a new task with a title and description.</li>
        <li><strong>Edit Task:</strong> Modify existing tasks to update their title or description.</li>
        <li><strong>Delete Task:</strong> Remove tasks from the database with a confirmation prompt.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Technologies Used</h3>
    <ul class="text-start">
        <li><strong>ASP.NET Core 7 MVC:</strong> Used for structuring the application following the Model-View-Controller pattern.</li>
        <li><strong>Entity Framework Core:</strong> ORM (Object-Relational Mapping) for database operations.</li>
        <li><strong>PostgreSQL:</strong> A powerful open-source relational database for data storage.</li>
        <li><strong>Bootstrap:</strong> For responsive and modern styling of the user interface.</li>
        <li><strong>Razor Views:</strong> To dynamically generate HTML content and handle UI logic.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>How It Works</h3>
    <ol class="text-start">
        <li><strong>Database:</strong> 
            <p>
                The application uses a `Tasks` table in a PostgreSQL database. This table contains the following columns:
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Id:</strong> Primary key for uniquely identifying tasks.</li>
                    <li><strong>Title:</strong> A short description of the task.</li>
                    <li><strong>Description:</strong> Detailed information about the task.</li>
                </ul>
            </p>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Controllers:</strong> 
            <p>
                The `TasksController` handles requests and coordinates communication between the user interface and the database:
                <ul>
                    <li>`Index`: Displays all tasks.</li>
                    <li>`Create`: Adds a new task to the database.</li>
                    <li>`Edit`: Updates existing task information.</li>
                    <li>`Delete`: Removes a task from the database.</li>
                </ul>
            </p>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Views:</strong> 
            <p>
                Razor views provide a clean and responsive user interface for interacting with the application. Each CRUD operation has its own view.
            </p>
        </li>
    </ol>

    <h3>Purpose of the Project</h3>
    <p>
        This project was created as part of a software development course to demonstrate the integration of modern web technologies 
        using ASP.NET Core MVC. It showcases the use of:
    </p>
    <ul class="text-start">
        <li>Database integration with Entity Framework Core.</li>
        <li>Dynamic content rendering using Razor Pages.</li>
        <li>Responsive design with Bootstrap.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>How to Get Started</h3>
    <p>
        Follow these steps to use the application:
        <ol>
            <li>Navigate to the <strong>Tasks</strong> page to see all available tasks.</li>
            <li>Use the <strong>Create</strong> button to add a new task.</li>
            <li>Click on <strong>Edit</strong> to modify a task's details.</li>
            <li>Click on <strong>Delete</strong> to remove a task permanently.</li>
        </ol>
    </p>

    <p>
        <a class="btn btn-primary" asp-area="" asp-controller="Tasks" asp-action="Index">Go to Tasks</a>
    </p>
</div>